title: Sainz crash ends 3rd practice session in Russia
text:
Luca Bruno Sainz crash ends 3rd practice session in Russia 
Ferrari driver Sebastian Vettel of Germany steers his car during the first free practice at the 'Sochi Autodrom' Formula One track , in Sochi, Russia, Friday, Oct. 9, 2015. The Formula one race will be held on Sunday. (AP Photo/Luca Bruno) Posted: Saturday, October 10, 2015 5:58 am Sainz crash ends 3rd practice session in Russia Associated Press | 0 comments 
SOCHI, Russia (AP) — A heavy crash for Toro Rosso's Carlos Sainz Jr. ended the final practice session at the Russian Grand Prix on Saturday. 
The Spanish driver speared into the barriers at the Sochi track and remained in the car, with part of the barriers covering the cockpit. The medical car attended. kAm%96 D6DD:@?
